info.structure_gel.building_tool_descrip:
• Used to modify blocks with many different modes and settings.
• Press %s while holding to open the GUI.
info.structure_gel.data_handler_descript:
• Generates objects in a structure based on the data within.
• Place the block and open the GUI to set data. You can test your data with the Generate button.
info.structure_gel.dynamic_spawner_descr:
• Behaves similar to a vanilla spawner, but uses pre-determined registered behaviors instead of storing spawning logic in the block itself. These behaviors must be registered by mods in code.
• Place the block and open the GUI to set data.
item.structure_gel.building_tool.info.op: • Press %s while holding to open the GUI.
item.structure_gel.building_tool.info.se: • For modes that require a block pallete you can press %s on a block to select it. You can also right click with an item held in your mouse onto this stack to select that block. If you use a block or item with an inventory, the inventory will be converted into a block pallete.
item.structure_gel.building_tool.info.zo: • You can change your reach distance by holding %s and using the mouse wheel.
item.structure_gel.building_tool.info.un: • You can undo previous actions with %s and redo them with %s.
info.structure_gel.building_tool.message: You do not have permission to use this item
One or more positions is in unloaded terrain
item.structure_gel.building_tool.mode.de:
• Replaces all matching blocks connected to the targeted block with the current pallete.

• %s on a block to select what to place.
• %s on a block to replace it.
item.structure_gel.building_tool.mode.se:
• %s to select the first corner.
• %s + %s to select the second corner.
• %s on a corner to move it. Hold %s to move the entire bounds.

• %s to select the first position.
• %s + %s to select the second position.
info.structure_gel.building_tool.go_back:
• Takes you back to the previous screen.
• Shortcut: %s
info.structure_gel.building_tool.select_: • Uses your current position as the first corner.
• Uses your current position as the second corner.
info.structure_gel.building_tool.edit_se:
• Allows editing the current selection.
• Shortcut: %s
• Expands the specified face of the current selection.
• Hold %s to move the selection instead.
• Shrinks the specified face of the current selection.
• Hold %s to move the selection instead.
info.structure_gel.building_tool.expand_:
• Expands the selected area in the direction you're facing.
• Hold %s to move the selection forward.
info.structure_gel.building_tool.block_p:
• The blocks that will be placed using this mode.
• %s to clear the pallete.
• Current pallete: %s
info.structure_gel.building_tool.propert: • Changes how far you're able to reach when this item is held.
• The length of this selection on the X axis.
• The height of this selection on the Y axis.
• The length of this selection on the Z axis.
• The chance of this entry being used.
• How far the selected area should be moved.
• When true, fills blocks below the plane that should be flooded.
• True if operation should extend to diagonal blocks. False if it should only see direct neighbors.
